        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The Heritage School - East Kolkata Township"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Manali D"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-11-04",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "2",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "We had planned to admit our child in Heritage School. So, we filled the form, information duly. They ask a list of questions on what is the parents' skill, achievements, if they have any significant social position. Possibly, these are taken into consideration. So, if you consider yourself plain and non-achiever, should think about it. We were quite sure if admission is accepted we will proceed with the same. However, it was such disappointment during the interview. Not only were we made to feel non-equal by, repeating that we are not from here in the city, and we ourselves did not study here, she asked us directly - why Heritage ( till this it was ok, but the Principal goes on to add -) \" when you are from small town\"? that was bothersome and quite an uncomfortable situation. I kept my cool, and answered best that came logically. Nevertheless, both my husband and I were offended. So, we were not even expecting the admission anyway. Surprisingly, our child was accepted. But we chose not to go ahead with the admission due to the bias shown. We have worked hard for the life we lead today and the small achievements we have got in life, but in no way, we want our child to grow in such an environment where there is a clear distinction of people, based on their capability and class. We believe in value-based learning. We do like how the school motivates the child to do big things in small ways, also the exposure they get to achieve so many things. But in no way, can they called the best with such arrogance.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
